Rating: 4
Some deflating will happen as it cools but there are a few things you can do to help avoid the significant deflate and crack. The first is don't overbeat your batter. Blend till it is combined but don't overmix. Baking in a water bath will help ensure even baking and when its done (or sometimes I'll do it when it is just slightly underdone) turn the oven off and crack the oven door. Leave the cheesecake in while the oven cools down. This will result in a slower cooling process and your cheesecake will be less likely to crack. GREAT Recipe. For thanksgiving i'm going to substitute sweet potatoes for the pumpkin for something new :).

