Rating: 4
We have made this pumpkin cheesecake every year since Thanksgiving 1990 -- it has become a signature dish for Thanksgiving Dinner at our house. However, for the last few years, we replaced the graham cracker crust with one made from gingersnaps. Unlikey! But the cheesecake freezes well -- cut slices, spread slightly on the bottom of the springform pan and freeze. When firm, wrap each slice and put back in the freezer in a freezer bag. Simply replace graham crumbs with an equal amount of gingersnap crumbs. The crust stands up to liquid better and keeps the crust from becoming soggy if you have left-overs.

