Rating: 4
This cheesecake is fabulous! I took a lot of hints from the comments, and it came out absolutely... fantastic. I used ginger snaps for the crust -- took a double handful of cookies along with a handful of pecans and threw them in the food processor, easy as that. I cut the butter in the crust by about 25%, so 3 tbsp. Prebaked 15 minutes at 350, came out perfect. I was liberal with the spices for the pumpkin filling, and I think it came out perfect. Probably half again as much cinnamon, nutmeg, etc as called for. Perfect. I used Bailey's Irish Cream instead of bourbon, as that's what I had on hand, and the flavor works great. Another change I made to the topping was to grate a bit of fresh ginger into the sour cream mixture. Everyone loved it -- the zing compliments the sweetness of the filling, as well as the ginger in the crust and filling. All in all... Four forks. Simply incredible, and I'll be making another for Christmas.

