Rating: 3
I made this lovely little number for Thanksgiving and what a hit! At another user's suggestion, I reduced the butter in the crust, but only by a smidge. I also roasted the pecans prior to using them by tossing with a couple tbs melted butter and some sea salt, then roasting at 350F for 15 min -- a step well worth the extra effort (I will never buy pre-roasted nuts again). The next time I make this cheesecake, I'll also increase the bourbon in the topping by 1 tsp for a little more zing. Overall, what a beauty! Everyone loved the way that the three layers were decreasingly sweet: against the candy-like crust, the filling seemed mildly sweet while the topping seemed to loose it's sweetness altogether, bringing out the tang of the sour cream and bourbon. Furthermore, the textures were fabulous. The crust was alternately crisp (it reminded me of praline) and moist with its own syrup, the cheesecake was both dense yet fluffy and the topping was smooth and subtly springy. Delicious!

