I have been making this recipe every Fall since it was published in 1990. It is an often asked for request for family gatherings. I recommend making it at least 48 hours in advance so that the flavors have time to blend and come out and the cheesecake has time to set and mold. When travelling far distances, I do not use the topping, I cart it in the pan and remove the sides when ready to serve. I sometimes just use cool whip with a little shot of bourbon and the pecans. When making the topping, I make the cake 48 hours ahead and frost it the night before I'm going to serve it.

