I have made this cheesecake several times and is it delicious and foolproof. I made the following changes with great success: (1) used a gingersnap cookie crust; (2) baked the cake in a bain marie (water bath) sealing the springform pan with heavy-duty foil; and (3) substituted Meyer's Dark Rum for the bourbon. This cheesecake is very rich but not too sweet. Best served in small slices - although I've had people ask for seconds!

