Delicious and creamy. Perfect for Thanksgiving. I halved the recipe and made it in a 6" springform and it came out beautifully. The reviewer tips were extremely helpful. I took their advice and made more crust, doubled the spices, sprinkled chopped pecans under the topping, and reduced the butter to avoid any seepage or sogginess. No problem with a water bath and 18" heavy duty foil. I'll certainly make this again, but we really couldn't taste the bourbon so I'll skip that and the topping in the future.

