Rating: 4
Everyone loved this cheesecake during Thanksgiving. I'm not a fan of pumpkin pie but really enjoyed this. I doubled the crust and used 6 tbsp. butter. Used 1 tbsp. to grease the springform pan. Baked the cheesecake at 450 for 10 minutes with a pan of hot water on the lower rack. Turned the temp. down to 350 and baked it for another 1hr 15 min. No cracks, turned out wonderfully. Candied some pecans to decorate with and crushed the rest to sprinkle on a simple vanilla bourbon whipped cream. Will definitely make again.

Rating: 4
Yummy with a capital Y!!! The only three things that I changed were the following: 1) Increase the crust!!!! The crust is undoubtedly the best part, and the above recipe only makes a very thin layer of crust. Make 2 times what the recipe calls for, except for the butter which you shouldn't double (you can just use the 1/2 stick of butter or increase to no more than 3/4 stick). Otherwise, you'll have a pool of butter leaking from the pan. 2) MIX IN GINGERSNAP COOKIES!!!! Make sure you use a 50-50 mix of gingersnap cookies and graham cracker crusts. Just today I won a contest at my office and people kept asking about the crust. It gives it a totally unique and scrumptious flavor! 3) GARNISH!!! If you're looking for a showstopper, it's fun to use something other than just nuts. I used chocolate leaves! Enjoy this divine dessert!

Rating: 4
This was the 2nd time that I made this cheesecake; the first time I followed the recipe exactly except for doubling the crust and the spices (nutmeg and cinnamon); the crust was soggy! However, it was still a delicious and spectacular cheesecake!! This time, my 2nd time, I did all of the above except I did not use brown sugar in the crust( just extra white sugar). And, I cooked the cheesecake for 10 minutes in a preheated 500' oven.. then I turned down the heat to 250' (leaving the oven door open until the temp. dropped )and cooked for 45 minutes longer. This kept the crust from being soggy, kept the cheesecake from cracking and made the cheesecake denser (instead of mouse-like) Yum!!!! I also followed other viewers suggestions by doubling the sugar in the sour cream topping. Thanks Epicurious!!!!

Rating: 4
