Rating: 3
After reading the other reviews before making this cake, I made the following modifications. The results were "Super Fantastic!" Not having bourbon I used Tuaca instead, and alot of it! In the cake I used 1/3 cup and left out the cream. I also added 1 tsp. more of cornstarch, no white sugar only lt. brown, and much more seasoning. This I did not measure, just made to taste. In the topping I again used Tuaca 1/4 cup, lt. brown sugar instead of white and added a small amount of corn starch. It was very hard to let this cake rest over night! It smelled so good while it was baking! Oh, I also added cinnamon and cloves to the crust along with extra graham cracker crumbs. I baked the crust for about 10 minutes at 350 then slightly cooled it before filling and baking the cake.

