I made this for our family's Christmas Day dessert and it was a hit. Made it 2 days in advance. I doubled the crust ingredients (including the butter) and then used all but about 1/2 cup of the entire mixture when forming the crust. The butter leaked as a few people mentioned. THANKS FOR THE HINT! I lined an 11" tart pan with foil and put the springform pan on top of that. Everyone really loved this recipe. It was so pretty too. I dusted it with finely grated dark chocolate. I added extra bourbon to the topping as it tasted great. I don't even like bourbon, but I liked it here. Couldn't taste it in the cheesecake itself. Also, this was incredibly simply to make. Finally, I took a few folks' suggestion and put a small bowl of boiling water in the oven (same shelf) and the cake did not have even the slightest crack in it. Just perfect. Bon Appetite!

