Rating: 3
Baked this for a potluck and they loved it, but they love every cheesecake. Here's how I adjusted the recipe - I increased the crust by 50% (all but the butter which stayed the same). I increased spices and vanilla also by 50%. I used ultrafine sugar in the topping and doubled the amount. Sprinkled pecans under the topping, and left off the pecan garnish (lazy). I wrapped the pan in foil, but that was unnecessary with the reduced proportion of butter in the crust - no butter leaked out. Although I pre-baked the crust 10 minutes, it still came out soggy. Next time I'll cover the crust with a layer of plain cheesecake batter because the pumpkin may be sogging the crust. To do that, I'll change only the order of ingredients in the filling - mix together only the sugars, cream cheese and eggs, pour a quarter of it on the crust, then add all the other ingredients to the bowl and mix some more, pour all of that on top of the plain cheesecake batter, etc. I didn't find my 9-inch pan so used a 10-inch pan, which took 45 minutes to bake. The bowl of boiling water in the oven prevented cracks, but next time I'll use a souffle dish since a Pyrex bowl seemed unstable. Next time I may bake it in two 7-inch pans unless there's a big party. (My friends love to hear I have an "extra" cheesecake.)

