Rating: 4
One of the joys of Epicurious is finding a great recipe and making subtle changes to make it your own. Such was the case with this scrumptious cheesecake which I made for Thanksgiving last year. After combing the recipes and reviews of all pumpkin cheesecakes, this was the winner. My touches - gingersnaps in lieu of graham crackers in the crust; kicked up the spices a bit and added cinammon; Drambuie for the liqueur; and a circle of tiny candied ginger pieces on the topping, concentric to the larger circle made by the pecans. I did wrap the springform pan in foil, alerted to the possibility of leakage and smoke in the oven. Good thing, as there was a pool of butter in the foil. While the outer crust was crisp, the bottom was a bit soft -- but no complaints from the crowd. It looked and tasted beautiful. A real keeper. This year, I made the Chocolate Cocnut Pecan Tart from this site. while delicious in its own right, everyone still raved about my cheesecake from last year!

