I made this dish the first time in an attempt to impress some very snooty in-laws. It was truely amazing how well it worked. In an instant I was being asked how to prepare not only this cheesecake, but a zillion other recips as well. Since then I make it once a year or by special request on special occasions. However I have since made some personal changes. Instead of canned pumpkin, I pick, cook, cut and scrape fresh ones if possible. Also, instead of using Burbon in the sour cream topping, I use Brandy, usually Christian bro's. Also, I have (when using too much brandy in things other than the cheesecake *hic*) gotten to the habit of instead of using the oven to carmelize the glaze, I use a mini blowtorch about 6-8 inches away, then chill immediately for 10 min, then cover and continue to chill overnight.

