Everyone raved about this recipe, which combines the traditional Thanksgiving pumpkin pie with the cheesecake. I decided not to add the Bourbon (I live in Bourbon country) because I did not see how it would complement the flavor of the cheesecake. After making this dish, I am glad I omitted the Bourbon. I also did not make the sour cream topping. One scoup of vanilla ice cream is great. Make sure that you use plain graham crackers and crush them. My crust was the weak part of the cheesecake.

